Arcadian Lab Website
Arcadian Lab Website is mainly informative, and its use is governed by the Terms and Conditions available
here
Why does Arcadian Lab collect data from its website?
Like on most websites, when you browse on
arcadianlab.com
certain information about your connection and device(s) is automatically collected for the website to operate properly.
Arcadian Lab and its partners also use cookies and similar technologies to analyze how our users interact with our services and administer the website. Cookies are small text files stored on your browser that allow the collection of non-personally identifiable information related to your navigation on a website.
You can control the use of cookies in your browser settings but if you choose to disable cookies it may affect certain websites’ functionalities.
What data does Arcadian Lab collect from its website?
For the purposes listed above the data that Arcadian Lab and its partners collect is limited to:
Browsing events and interactions with the website’s contents and services
Anonymized IP address and technical information related to your browser and/or device (user agent)
Information you provide us with voluntarily when you contact Arcadian Lab
Analytics and third party cookies
Arcadian Lab uses Google Analytics to collect information related to the web traffic on our website. This service allows us to measure the performance and proper functioning of our website and to provide you with a better experience. Arcadian Lab made sure to configure this tool in such a way that the information collected for this purpose is anonymized in a way that does not allow identifying any end-users of our website.
For more information on the data protection and privacy aspects of these analytics services, you can refer to Google specific policy accessible
here
and opt-out from Google Analytics data collection
here
.
Social networks and other communication tools
Our website also offers communication tools allowing users to share content on social networks. When you interact with such social media widgets or “share buttons”, these social network companies may collect information about you and/or your device and connection. Your interactions with these services are governed by the respective privacy policies of the companies providing these services. For more information on the data protection and privacy practices of these companies, you can refer to their specific policies listed below:
Facebook:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/
LinkedIn:
https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy
Security and other important information
How long does Arcadian Lab keep your data?
Personal data collected, received, and processed for the purposes described in this policy is not kept longer than necessary by Arcadian Lab.
Arcadian Lab does not retain user level data for more than 13 months except for the data collected for the purpose of its first-party analytics tool, which can be stored up to 25 months based on the guidelines of our Supervisory Data Protection Authority.
Children data
Arcadian Lab never knowingly or willingly collects any personal data concerning children under 13 years of age.
International transfers
Some of the partners and processors referred to in this policy are located outside of Canada.
In such case, we ensure that:
The personal data is transferred to countries recognized as offering an equivalent level of protection or,
For personal data transferred outside of countries recognized by the Canadian authorities as having a sufficient level of protection, any of the mechanisms offering appropriate guarantees is used, for which provision is made by applicable regulations, and notably the adoption of the standard contractual clauses.
For more information about international transfers and the safeguards in place, you can contact us at
info@arcadianlab.com.
What rights do you have?
Your personal information belongs to you, and we will make sure your rights are respected. You can contact us at
info@arcadianlab.com.
at any time to ask for a copy of your data, to withdraw your consent, or to obtain the deletion of the information we keep for you.
Consent withdrawal and opt-out of sale of information
You can change your consent status at any time from the Privacy Settings available on Arcadian Lab mobile games and applications.
Please note that if Arcadian Lab does not sell the personal information of its users, we may share it with third parties such as analytics and advertising companies to improve and personalize your experience and adapt the content and ads of our services.
Adjusting your consent settings within Arcadian Lab apps and games will allow you to block the collection of data for these purposes and will de facto prevent the sharing of information with our analytics and/or advertising partners.
Access right
Upon request, Arcadian Lab will provide you with information about whether we hold any of your personal information. You may access or request deletion of your personal information directly in Arcadian Lab mobile apps or by contacting Arcadian Lab Data Protection Officer as indicated in the “Contact” section below. We will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe.
Rectification and erasure
You may request Arcadian Lab the rectification of inaccurate personal data concerning you, as well as the completion of incomplete personal data. You may also request Arcadian Lab to erase without undue delay your personal data when it is no longer necessary for Arcadian Lab to retain such data.
In order for your data to be erased or rendered inaccessible you can either:
Reset your mobile advertising identifier (IDFA on iOS, GAAID on Android) or activate “Limit Ad Tracking” in your device’s settings to make previously collected data non-linkable to you or your device anymore and limit further data collection if you choose to enable the “Limit Ad Tracking” option.
Contact Arcadian Lab Data Protection Officer, as indicated in the “Contact” section below, to have the data previously collected by Arcadian Lab on you and/or your device permanently erased or anonymized.
Portability
Upon request, Arcadian Lab will provide you with the personal data that you provided to us and, if possible, will communicate this information directly to another data controller of your choice in a portable format when the processing is based on consent or contract.
Right to lodge a complaint
You may lodge a complaint with a Data Protection Authority. Arcadian Lab being a Canadian company, our supervisory authority is in Canada: Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada
(OPC)
Contact
Arcadian Lab Inc. is the Data Controller
You can contact our DPO at:
info@arcadianlab.com
Data Protection Officer – Arcadian Lab – 1200 - 900 W Hastings St, Vancouver, BC V6C 1E5, Canada.
